'''''Six-Gun Shootout''''' (shown on the title screen as '''''Sixgun Shootout''''')<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Six-Gun Shootout |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-six-gun-shootout_4685.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref> is a video game written by Jeff Johnson for [[Atari 8-bit computers]] and published in 1985 by [[Strategic Simulations]].<ref name=giantlist/>

==Gameplay==
''Six-Gun Shootout'' is a game in which man-to-man combat is simulated in ten scenarios set in the [[Wild West]].<ref name="CGW23"/>

==Reception==
Johnny Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "SG is an relatively simple, fast-moving and enjoyable game. It is satisfying and clear-cut in its determination of victory points and victory."<ref name="CGW23">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=September 1985 |volume=1 |issue=23 |pages=37, 47}}</ref>

